==English==

===Noun===
'''goon'''
# A [[thug]], a usually muscular henchman with very little intelligence.  The term ''goon'' rose to prominence in this context thanks to frequent usage in [[Popeye]].
#Guardians of the Oglala Sioux Nation, thugs employed by the corrupt tribal chairman of [[Pine Ridge Indian Reservation]], Dick Wilson, during the 1970s.
#An [[Ice Hockey]]player who has very little skills other than fighting. The amount of goons has decreased and today there are no pure goons in the [[NHL]] as a more skilled [[Enforcer]]-type players have replaced them.
#'Hired Goon' A mercenary thug hired by bosses to break strikes. Similar to;
#'Goon Squads' Sometimes used by police departments to refer to specific police who suppress protests.